featured_reviews.review_id:
Beautiful Branch Manara, Riviera.
Great View as well.

Starbucks needs no recommendations.
One of the best if not the Best.

To the Management,
Unfortunately, at this "Manara Branch" specifically we had an unpleasant surprise.
First we were requested to leave our indoor table because someone felt like cleaning the premises while we were seated.
Then once we needed to use their toilets we were denied access again, because the same person had already "shattaff" cleaned, while their sitting area was still full... At 21h40 on December 22nd, 2022.
Obviously we had to leave.
We will still go to Starbucks.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Dunkin' Donuts in Saida is a true gem and a testament to the brand's commitment to excellence. This Dunkin' Donuts outlet offers an exceptional experience that keeps customers coming back for more.

The moment you step into Dunkin' Donuts Saida, you are greeted with the enticing aroma of freshly brewed coffee and the sweet scent of warm, freshly baked donuts. The ambiance is inviting and cozy, making it the perfect spot for a quick coffee fix, a leisurely snack, or a delightful meet-up with friends.

The staff at Dunkin' Donuts Saida are a standout feature, offering warm and friendly service that instantly puts you at ease. They are knowledgeable about the menu and are more than happy to assist you with your choices or offer recommendations.

The menu is a wonderful fusion of Dunkin' Donuts' timeless classics and unique local flavors that cater to the diverse palate of the Lebanese people. The donuts are a work of art, with an array of flavors and textures that leave your taste buds dancing with delight. Whether you prefer the classic glaze or the intriguing Lebanese-inspired creations, each bite is an explosion of flavor.

The coffee at Dunkin' Donuts Saida is consistently top-notch, delivering that perfect caffeine kick that you crave. It's clear that quality is a top priority, ensuring that every cup is a sip of pure satisfaction.

The clean and well-maintained interior adds to the overall appeal, making it a comfortable and hygienic place to enjoy your treats. Families, friends, and solo patrons alike are drawn to Dunkin' Donuts Saida, making it a popular destination for everyone.

In conclusion, Dunkin' Donuts Saida is more than just a donut and coffee shop; it's an experience. It's a place where you can indulge in the flavors of Dunkin' Donuts while enjoying the warmth and charm of Lebanese hospitality. If you're in Saida and in need of a delectable treat and a warm atmosphere, Dunkin' Donuts Saida is the place to be.

Finding a solution to smoking indoors will grant this shop its 5th star, in my opinion.
